/**
--------------------------------------------------------------------
âœ… Problem: Symmetric Tree (LeetCode #101)

Given the root of a binary tree, check whether it is symmetric
around its center (i.e., it is a mirror of itself).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
Input:
      1
     / \
    2   2
   / \ / \
  3  4 4  3

Output: true

--------------------------------------------------------------------
âœ… Approach: Recursive Mirror Check

ðŸ’¡ **Idea:**
A binary tree is symmetric if:
1ï¸âƒ£ The left and right subtrees are mirror images of each other.
2ï¸âƒ£ That means:
   - left->val == right->val
   - left->left mirrors right->right
   - left->right mirrors right->left

We perform a recursive DFS check for each pair of nodes.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
âœ… Implementation:
*/

class Solution {
public:
    bool helper(TreeNode* left, TreeNode* right) {
        // Both are null â†’ symmetric
        if (left == nullptr && right == nullptr)
            return true;

        // One is null, other not â†’ not symmetric
        if (left == nullptr || right == nullptr)
            return false;

        // Values differ â†’ not symmetric
        if (left->val != right->val)
            return false;

        // Recurse on mirrored children
        return helper(left->left, right->right) &&
               helper(left->right, right->left);
    }

    bool isSymmetric(TreeNode* root) {
        // An empty tree is symmetric
        if (!root) return true;

        // Compare left and right subtrees
        return helper(root->left, root->right);
    }
};

/**
--------------------------------------------------------------------
âœ… Dry Run Example:

Input:
      1
     / \
    2   2
   / \ / \
  3  4 4  3

helper(2, 2) â†’ equal  
â†’ helper(3, 3) â†’ equal â†’ returns true  
â†’ helper(4, 4) â†’ equal â†’ returns true  
âœ… Final Output = true

--------------------------------------------------------------------
âœ… Time Complexity:
O(N) â€” Each node is visited once.

âœ… Space Complexity:
O(H) â€” Recursive call stack (H = height of tree).

âœ… Concepts Used:
- Recursion
- Mirror comparison (DFS)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
